Package ohos.smartcomm

Class MultiPathManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.smartcomm.MultiPathManager

  • public class MultiPathManager
extends Object
    Manages multiple paths in smart communication.

    This class uses the singleton pattern. The getInstance method can be used to obtain the MultiPathManager object.

    This class provides methods to manage multiple paths, for example, enabling or disabling multipath.

      • enableMultipathFlow

        public int enableMultipathFlow​(String packageName,
                               String flowParamJson,
                               String multipathParamJson,
                               IMultiPathCallback callback)
                        throws RemoteException
        Enables multipath.

        This method can enable multipath based on an application or a combination of IP address and port number. If an application is specified, multipath is enabled for all flows from the application; if a combination of IP address and port number is specified, multipath is enabled for all flows from the application to the IP address and port number.

        Parameters:
        packageName - Indicates the package name of the application for which multipath is enabled.
        flowParamJson - Indicates flow parameters in JSON format. The parameters include MULTIPATH_FLOW_SCALE, MULTIPATH_IP_ADDRESS, MULTIPATH_IP_PORT, MULTIPATH_IP_CARRIER, MULTIPATH_IP_DEPLOYTYPE, MULTIPATH_IP_GROUP, and MULTIPATH_FLOW_TYPE.
        multipathParamJson - Indicates multipath parameters in JSON format. The parameters include MULTIPATH_POLICY_TYPE, MULTIPATH_USER_ID, MULTIPATH_SCENARIO_FLAG, MULTIPATH_PARAM_RTT, and MULTIPATH_PARAM_BANDWIDTH.
        callback - Indicates the callback that is automatically called when a multipath switching occurs.
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if multipath is enabled; returns -1 if multipath is not enabled; returns -2 if parameters are incorrect; returns -3 if the remote call of this method fails.
        Throws:
        RemoteException
        Since:
        1

      • disableMultipath

        public int disableMultipath​(String packageName,
                            String flowParamJson)
                     throws RemoteException
        Disables multipath.

        This method can disable multipath based on an application or a combination of IP address and port number.

        Parameters:
        packageName - Indicates the package name of the application for which multipath is disabled.
        flowParamJson - Indicates flow parameters in JSON format. The parameters include MULTIPATH_FLOW_SCALE, MULTIPATH_IP_ADDRESS, MULTIPATH_IP_PORT, MULTIPATH_IP_CARRIER, MULTIPATH_IP_DEPLOYTYPE, MULTIPATH_IP_GROUP, and MULTIPATH_FLOW_TYPE.
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if multipath is disabled; returns -1 if multipath is not disabled; returns -2 if parameters are incorrect; returns -3 if the remote call of this method fails.
        Throws:
        RemoteException
        Since:
        1
